docs.description: Germany per capita GNI at current prices - US dollars. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. For more about the National Accounts Main Aggregates database, see http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/introduction.asp. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. For more about the National Accounts Main Aggregates database, see http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/introduction.asp. The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx

The data here covers the period from 1990 onwards. Data prior to 1990, would be available at http://unstats.un.org/unsd/energy/edbase.htm. For more information, please see http://unstats.un.org/unsd/energy/default.htm
column_names: Date
Changes in stocks (metric tons; thousand)

docs.name: Manufacture Of Woven Wool Fabrics In United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland
docs.description: Data Sources: UNICSD and FAOSTAT.  The United Nations Industrial Commodity Statistics Database provides annual statistics on the production of major industrial commodities by country.  Data are provided in terms of physical quantities as well as monetary value. FAOSTAT collects and publishes data relating to food and agriculture for 200 countries and more than 200 primary products.
column_names: Date
Mil. USD
THOUSAND SQUARE METRES

docs.name: Trade in Vehicles Other Than Railway, Tramway - Sri Lanka
docs.description: Trade in Vehicles Other Than Railway, Tramway - Sri Lanka. This data employs the subheadings of the original Harmonized System (HS1992). The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962. For more info, please see http://comtrade.un.org/db/mr/rfGlossaryList.aspx
